  We study the problem of estimating E(g(X)), where g is a real-valued function
of d variables and X is a d-dimensional Gaussian vector with a given covariance
matrix. We present a new unbiased estimator for E(g(X)) that combines the
randomized dimension reduction technique with principal components analysis.
Under suitable conditions, we prove that our algorithm outperforms the standard
Monte Carlo method by a factor of order d.
